The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Conspiracy in Puri kill

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Barasat, June 24: Congress leader Somen Mitra today said there was deep-rooted political conspiracy in the murder of Tapas Mitra, the councillor shot dead on Puri beach.

 Tapas Mitra, 40, was a councillor of Bongaon municipality in North 24-Parganas and also a contractor. 

 A murder accused, he had been out on bail and had to report to police periodically. 

 Somen said: He was murdered because of a long-standing political rivalry and the truth will come out in a day or two.

 The body was brought to Champapukur in Bongaon, about 70 km from Calcutta, this morning. Somen was there to pay his last respects to the other Mitra.

 The Congress-Trinamul Congress alliance controls the 21-member municipal board with 12 members.




